2026-04-10 | Find Increasing Triplet Subsequence

Question
Return any valid increasing subsequence of size 3.

	Approach
1.	Create two arrays:
		leftMin[i] → smallest element before i  
		rightMax[i] → largest element after i  

2.	Fill leftMin:
		leftMin[0] = arr[0]  
		leftMin[i] = min(leftMin[i-1], arr[i])  

3.	Fill rightMax:
		rightMax[n-1] = arr[n-1]  
		rightMax[i] = max(rightMax[i+1], arr[i])  

4.	For each index j:
		if leftMin[j] < arr[j] < rightMax[j]:
			return {leftMin[j], arr[j], rightMax[j]}  

5.	If none found → return empty  

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(n)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> find3Numbers(vector<int>& arr) {

        int n = arr.size();

        vector<int> leftMin(n), rightMax(n);

        leftMin[0] = arr[0];
        for(int i = 1; i < n; i++){
            leftMin[i] = min(leftMin[i-1], arr[i]);
        }

        rightMax[n-1] = arr[n-1];
        for(int i = n-2; i >= 0; i--){
            rightMax[i] = max(rightMax[i+1], arr[i]);
        }

        for(int i = 1; i < n-1; i++){
            if(leftMin[i] < arr[i] && arr[i] < rightMax[i]){
                return {leftMin[i], arr[i], rightMax[i]};
            }
        }

        return {};
    }
};

	Key Insight
For each element as middle:
- check if a smaller exists on left  
- and a larger exists on right  

This guarantees an increasing triplet in O(n) time.
